fulltitle: In 2014 two Dutch students Lisanne Froon (22) and Kris Kremers (21) disappeared while hiking

comments.text:
In 2014 two Dutch students Lisanne Froon (22) and Kris Kremers (21) disappeared while hiking the Pianista Trail near Boquete, Panama.

Ten days later a backpack was found by a river containing their phones, a camera, passports, cash and even their bras, untouched as if carefully placed.

Phone records showed 77 desperate calls to emergency numbers, none of which connected. Days later someone kept trying to unlock one phone with the wrong PIN, as if it was no longer in their hands.

The camera revealed over 90 disturbing photos, many taken deep in the jungle at night. Rocks, branches, darkness, and one chilling image of a girls head with blood near the temple.

Weeks later Lisannes severed foot was discovered still inside her boot, along with bones from both girls that had been mysteriously bleached.

To this day nobody knows the truth. Was it a tragic accident, a brutal crime, or something much darker hiding in the Panamanian jungle?
